A Manager / Assistant Manager, Laboratory Administration & Compliance is now required as a result of business growth:
Responsibilities:
Responsible for all laboratory management related activities, including equipment re-allocation & disposal, and chemical & clinical wastes disposal;
Maintain routine laboratory operations, including equipment maintenance & calibration, inventory taking and laboratory record maintenance;
Plan and execute quality control assignment on various research & development activities;
Perform risk assessment of operations and evaluate adequacy of internal controls;
Carry out reviews and investigations, provide findings and recommendations to operation teams and top management;
Timely follow up the implementation of recommendations / corrective action plans;
Deliver trainings on integrity and compliance and share of audit requirements to team members;
Assist in laboratory accreditation application and implementation of standard operating procedures;
Liaise with team members and internal audit department on quality matters.
 Requirements:
A degree or above in Science, Engineering or related disciplines;
A minimum of 5 years’ relevant experience, some exposure of regulatory compliance / audit in academia or industry is desirable;
Hands-on experience in laboratory operation and equipment management is preferable;
Proficient in various aspects of laboratory management, including laboratory building services, electrical and mechanical services, laboratory safety, principle, regulation, compliance and ISO international standards;
Self-motivated and team oriented with problem solving ability and excellent documentation skills;
Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese; 
Candidates with less experience will be considered for Assistant Manager role.
Thank you for your interest in a career with CK Life Sciences. Competitive compensation and benefits package will be offered to the right candidate. We operate a 5-day workweek, and our benefits cover retirement, health and life. Regular shuttle bus service is also provided with pick-ups and drop-offs at designated and convenient locations. 
To apply for our position, you should write, enclosing a current resume to Chief Manager, Human Resources & Administration, CK Life Sciences Limited, 2 Dai Fu Street, Tai Po Industrial Estate, Hong Kong or by clicking the APPLY NOW button. For more company information, please visit www.ck-lifesciences.com. 
We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates.  Personal data collected will be treated in strictest confidence and handled confidentially by authorized personnel for recruitment-related purposes within the Group.

THE JOB
Reporting to the Director, Elite Training Science and Technology, the Sport Biomechanist will be responsible for the following duties:
To lead and manage the operation of the Sport Biomechanics and Technology Centre, and ensure service models reflecting international best practice standards and are appropriately integrated with the allied scientific, medical, and athlete affairs service units according to the biopsychosocial operating model of the  Elite Training Science and Technology Division (ETSTD);
To plan and implement state-of-the-art applied sport biomechanics services to support and enhance elite sports training;
To provide on-field support at local and overseas training and competition;
To plan and implement discipline specific educational programmes such as lectures and workshops for both athletes and coaches;
To participate and contribution to the ETSTD applied research programme;
To contribute discipline specific expertise to the HKSIL Talent Identification Programmes;
To represent the HKSIL at local and international conferences, scientific seminars and meetings, and in the international scientific literature through scientific publications; and
To assist in the organization of the annual HKSIL International Scientific Symposium.
THE REQUIREMENTS
A doctoral / master degree in sport biomechanics, sports scienc, physics, engineering or a relevant discipline;
A minimum of 10 years’ relevant working experience in practical fields;
Substantial experience in planning and implementing state-of-the-art applied sport biomechanics services to enhance elite sports training
Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese.  Fluency in Cantonese and Putonghua;
Good communication and interpersonal skills;
Effective and efficient team player; and
Able to work in irregular hours and perform under pressure.  

[Applicants who have responded to the previous advertisements need not re-apply. Their applications are being considered accordingly.]



